Come to Calgary’s Largest "Own Your Own Business" Event!
See the most successful franchises + brand new opportunities from every industry. 
2 Days Only! Meet Face to Face with Proven Businesses
Proven, money making businesses that are now expanding in Calgary are here to meet new potential owners. This is your only opportunity to meet with the hottest businesses face to face. Ask questions and get the information you need in a no pressure environment. Be there, find the businesses that excite you, shake hands and say hello!
Make More Money: Franchising is the EASY Way to Own a Business
Buying a franchise or proven business opportunity eliminates all the hard work of opening a business independently and will help you avoid much of the risk of starting a new business. name: PETRA
description_without_html:
PETRA live in concert - 50th Anniversary Tour
Dates:     Saturday, November 18th at 7pm
                Sunday, November 19th at 7pm
Where:    Bow Valley Baptist Church,  54 West Aarsby Road,  Cochrane, Alberta
Tickets go on sale to the public on Tuesday, September 19th at 9AM.
 
Doors open at 6:00pm
Be a part of this once in a lifetime concert event. This is going to sell out quickly so get your tickets now!
Petra, one of the most popular and influential bands in Christian music history, who retired from touring in 2005, is doing a limited run of tour dates to celebrate 50 years as a band. Whether they were the band you grew up with, or you just discovered them you will not want to miss this concert.
It is rare for any artist to last 50 years, but for a band who has released 24 albums over their illustrious career, sold over 10 million records, garnered four Grammys, ten Doves, an induction into the Gospel Music Hall of Fame - it’s relatively unheard of.
Petra will be playing hits from their 50-year history as well as reminiscing about changes in the culture, the church and Christian music. Come join us and be a part of Christian music history!
Assigned seating floor and balcony and Backstage tickets are available!  (Backstage Tickets include front and center seating  plus a backstage meet and greet with the bands before the concert)
Special Guest: REVIVAL

name: A Louisiana Hayride Christmas
description_without_html:
You will LOVE A Louisiana Hayride Christmas!
 
Get in the Christmas spirit with the incredibly talented cast of the Louisiana Hayride Show. After 13 years of successful shows across Western Canada, the cast and crew of the Louisiana Hayride Show are bringing their very special Christmas production to you!
 
On stage to entertain you will be Elvis Presley, Patsy Cline, Roy Orbison, Crystal Gayle, Buddy Holly, Shania Twain and more! They’ll be singing their big hits as well as their favorite Christmas songs, such as Blue Christmas, Let It Snow, Pretty Paper, Have Yourself A Merry Little Christmas and White Christmas.
 
In addition to enjoying your favorite ‘characters’ from the Louisiana Hayride Show and a few of the show’s most popular songs like I Walk the Line, Crazy, Hound Dog, Sixteen Tons, That’ll Be the Day and Pretty Woman, in this special Christmas edition you’ll be treated to the incredible vocals of the Louisiana Hayride cast as they sing as themselves!
 
Andrea Anderson will bring tears to your eyes with her incredible versions of Oh Holy Night and How Great Thou Art.  William Brookfield is back for this Christmas show and he and Gil Risling do a wonderful rendition of Away In A Manger and Gil’s vocals and William’s instrumentation on Hark the Herald Angels will leave you breathless!.
 
Woven throughout the songs are fascinating tidbits of information (with a Christmas twist), delightfully presented by your host and creator of the show, Lori Risling. This show will take you on a magical Christmas journey, a delight from start to finish.You will Love the Songs, You will Love the Stories!!!  Tell your friends and family and get your tickets now before the show sell out! All info available at www.hayrideshow.com or email loririsling@hotmail.com

name: Corporate Box Seating - Calgary National Bank Challenger 2023
description_without_html:
THE CHALLENGER 2023
The Calgary National Bank Challenger (The Challenger) event will return to the OSTEN & VICTOR Alberta Tennis Centre from November 5 to 12, 2023. This will be the second time the popular tournament will be held as a combined….
Men’s & Women’s Professional Event
The Challenger event has quickly gained a reputation as one of the premier sporting events in Alberta and one of best ATP Challenger tournament events in the world. It is the largest professional men’s & women’s combined indoor tennis tournament in Canada. In 2023 we will host our International Tennis Federation (ITF) Women’s Pro Circuit Event featuring many of the best up-and-coming female players in the world. This world class event is a must attend event, featuring many of the best up-and-coming and established stars on the ATP, ITF and WTA World Tours.
This event prides itself on bringing the tennis world and the Calgary community together, hosting on-site activities, engaging local tennis clubs and providing opportunities to get on court while the tournament is on.
 
 
Policies

There will be no assigned seating during the ATP Challenger. 
All tickets are general admission on a first come-first-serve basis with the exception of Box Holders who will be given assigned seats/tickets.

Spectator Etiquette

Please remain in your seat until the end of play and only leave your seat during a player change-over.
Please refrain from making noise during play.
Smoking is not permitted within the grounds of the Alberta Tennis Centre.
Turn cell phones to silent or vibrate mode.
Do not use flash photography from the stands.

Code of Conduct

Alberta Tennis Centre, Tennis Canada, Tennis Alberta and the ATP Tour are committed to creating a safe, comfortable and enjoyable experience for all fans attending.
We ask fans to be respectful of those around them and that they conduct themselves appropriately at all times.
Guests will be denied entry if intoxicated/impaired or in possession of and illegal substance.
Any other conduct deemed inappropriate by tournament organizers may result in ejection and/or further legal action. 
Fans who are ejected will have their tickets revoked and will not be compensated in any way.

Parking:

Only box holders with parking passes are allowed to park on the premises
Public transit or car pooling is recommended
Parking available at Carriage House overflow parking lot
Allow ample time to walk to the Alberta Tennis Centre
Some street parking is available; please review posted signs on the street
Towing is enforced

Terms & Conditions 
No ticket holder or spectator may: (a) continually collect, disseminate, transmit, publish or release from the grounds of the Tournament any match scores or related statistical data during match play (from the commencement of a match through its conclusion for any commercial, betting or gambling purpose); and (b) film, photograph, broadcast, stream, publish, transmit and/or otherwise offer to the public (or assist any third party in offering to the public), on a live or on a delayed basis, in whole or in part, and whether on a free basis or subject to payment, any sound recording, photograph, video footage, motion picture, film and/or other audio-visual content captured by any mean whatsoever inside the Tournament site (except as it is allow in the Tournament Accreditation Policy). The continual use of laptop computers or other handheld electronic devices within the confines (spectator area) of the tournament match courts is prohibited. The exception of this provision is properly credentialed media, tournament vendors and tournament staff when used in the performance of their duties.
COVID-19 Notice
You understand that the event for which you purchase a ticket shall be presented in accordance with applicable public health conditions as of the date of such event and which may change at any time as determined by federal, provincial, or local government agencie;  such requirements may include, without limitation, changes to capacity, attendance procedures and entry requirements, such as proof of vaccination and/or a negative COVID-19 test, and other protective measures such as requiring attendees to wear face coverings. If any Holder does not comply with any laws, mandates, health orders or directives, promoter or venue terms, conditions or rules, then the promoter or venue operator may refuse admission or require any Holder to leave the venue and you/Holder will not be entitled to a refund.
Event Cancellations/Postponements
Events may be postponed or canceled for a variety of reasons.  If you hold tickets to an event that is postponed or canceled, we encourage you to directly contact the Alberta Tennis Centre (ATC) to obtain information about postponed dates of the event and whether there is an applicable refund.

Refunds will generally be issued if an event is canceled and not rescheduled, however, ATC reserves the right to retain various fees and charges paid by buyers or sellers on our Service, even if an event is canceled and not rescheduled.  Refunds will be issued by ATC to the Payment Method on file that was used to make your purchase.
If an event is rescheduled, we will try to offer a ticket with the same value or in the same location as the one you originally purchased, although that is not always possible.

 
2023 Calgary National Bank Challenger Ticket Validation and Transferability Policy 
Section 1: General Information about Ticket Transferability

All Calgary National Bank Challenger (the event) general admission tickets are transferable BEFORE being validated.
General admission tickets include:

Daily tickets
Weekend passes
Weekly passes


All daily general admission tickets can be transferred to other people BEFORE it is validated. Once it is validated for the day, the ticket cannot be transferred or be used to enter the event venue anymore.
A weekend pass is valid for November 11, November 12, and November 13. The weekend pass can be validated once each day. A weekend pass can be transferred to other people before it is validated for the day. Once it is validated for the day, the pass cannot be transferred or be used to enter the event venue on that day.
A weekly pass is valid for all days from November 5 to November 13. The weekly pass can be validated once each day. A weekly pass can be transferred to other people before it is validated for the day. Once it is validated for the day, the pass cannot be transferred or used to enter the event venue for the Day.
Spectators are not allowed to duplicate the ticket by photocopying, scanning, or screenshotting.

 
Section 2: Ticket Validation and Re-entering

The general admission tickets will only be validated during the event (November 5 – 12, 2023). Tickets cannot and will not be validated before or after the event.
The general admission tickets will be validated at the entrance of the event venue (OSTEN & VICTOR Alberta Tennis Centre, 295 90th Ave SE Calgary, AB T2J 0A1) only.
The general admission tickets will be validated by the volunteers or staff manually or digitally with a ticket scanner.

Manual validation: volunteers or staff will hole-punch or mark the valid physical tickets (a printed event ticket) on the date the ticket states and stamp the ticket holder’s arm with a stamp.
Digital validation: volunteers or staff will validate the digital tickets (a printout of a digital copy or shown on a digital device) by scanning the barcode/QR code and stamp the ticket holder’s arm with a stamp


Each daily general admission tickets can only be validated (manually or digitally) once.
Each weekend pass and weekly pass can only be validated once each day of the event.
After the ticket or the pass is being validated for the day, ticket holders/spectator can re-enter the event venue by showing the ticketing volunteer or staff the stamped image on their arm.
The validation stamp image will be changed and updated each day when the gate opens.

For information for the box holders, please look out for a letter from the Tournament Director, Danny Da Costa. Danny will be sending you the information directly in the near future.

name: Shaun Majumder - The Love Tour
description_without_html: Raised in rural Newfoundland Canada, Shaun Majumder has been a performer his entire life. After leaving his hometown of Burlington (Pop 350) and moving to Mississauga Ontario at the age of thirteen, Shaun acted in his first stage play in the 8th Grade (Grade 8 in Canada). Immediately he was hooked. He continued theatre throughout high school, winning several awards at festivals for his many performances. But according to the adults around him, there was no future in this acting thing. So, Shaun followed the guidance of his teachers and did what most did; went to university with the hopes of a career finding him.After one year of partying and taking general arts classes, Shaun quickly realized his true passion was acting, so he abandoned his safety net and went for it.He found early success as a Standup Comedian and host, landing his first gigs with YTV (Canada’s Nickelodeon) as a host/PJ for five years, along with CBC’s Just For Laughs comedy series. He continued to book small roles in Film and TV and in 2003 he Joined the cast of CBC’s This Hour Has 22 minutes where he spent seventeen seasons.For the past twenty plus years, Shaun has found success on both sides of the border. A few noteworthy performances include his work as Detective Vik Mahajan in the ABC’s critically acclaimed crime drama, Detroit 1-8-7. His role as Andrew Palmer on NBC’s The Firm starring alongside Josh Lucas and Juliette Lewis. As Hassan Numair on FOX’s 24. His comedy roles include starring in the Sketch Comedy Series Cedric The Entertainer Presents, The Farrelly Brothers Unhitched, ABC’s Married Not Dead, NBC’s Nevermind Nirvana, and CBC’s Hatching Matching and Dispatching.He currently stars alongside Harold Parineau, Catalina Sandino Moreno and Eion Bailey, in the EPIX Sci Fi/Horror series FROM playing Father Khatri.Shaun resides in Los Angeles with his wife Shelby Fenner, his two daughters Mattis Maple and Eslyn Willow and their two Boston terriers Jazzy and Freddy.

No Thanks is a high-energy house duo that produces their sound from the Canadian West Coast at full tilt. Giuliano Rascan and Dejan Zoric’s collaboration merges the gap between tech, bass, and pop genres to curate house that is undeniably rooted in West Coast influence.
While the standard house rules apply, No Thanks lures their listeners into an auditory playground that is vocal driven and stylized with high pitch, tight drums, and low bass lines. Their approach to music is instrumentally nuanced, but their philosophy is simple: there’s something for everyone. This duo’s international reach has generated a global call for West Coast house, and No Thanks is responding.
Latest release "Freak" dropped just under 3 weeks ago and has already hit 300k streams and a number of big Spotify playlists.
Highlights include DJ support from Marten Horger, DJ Susan, Neon Steve, Dr Fresch, Wax Motif, Chris Lake, Biscits, David Guetta, CID, BIJOU, Tiesto, FREAK ON, Westend, Loud Luxury, Bingo Players, ACRAZE, Kyle Watson, 3lau and more!
